.TH "BroadcastChannel" "JS" "June 3, 2024" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
BroadcastChannel \- BroadcastChannel
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]BroadcastChannel\f[B]\f[R] interface represents a named
channel that any browsing context of a given origin can subscribe to.
It allows communication between different documents (in different
windows, tabs, frames or iframes) of the same origin.
Messages are broadcasted via a \f[CR]message\f[R] event fired at all
\f[CR]BroadcastChannel\f[R] objects listening to the channel, except the
object that sent the message.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.TP
\f[B]BroadcastChannel()\f[R]
Creates an object linking to the named channel.
.SH INSTANCE PROPERTIES
\f[I]This interface also inherits properties from its parent,
\f[CI]EventTarget\f[I].\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]BroadcastChannel.name\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
Returns a string, the name of the channel.
.SH INSTANCE METHODS
\f[I]This interface also inherits methods from its parent,
\f[CI]EventTarget\f[I].\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]BroadcastChannel.postMessage()\f[R]
Sends the message, of any type of object, to each
\f[CR]BroadcastChannel\f[R] object listening to the same channel.
.TP
\f[B]BroadcastChannel.close()\f[R]
Closes the channel object, indicating it won\[cq]t get any new messages,
and allowing it to be, eventually, garbage collected.
.SH EVENTS
\f[I]This interface also inherits events from its parent,
\f[CI]EventTarget\f[I].\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]message\f[R]
Fired when a message arrives on the channel.
Also available via the \f[CR]onmessage\f[R] property.
.TP
\f[B]messageerror\f[R]
Fired when a message arrives that can\[cq]t be deserialized.
Also available via the \f[CR]onmessageerror\f[R] property.
